Location Intelligence & Store Expansion Analysis

🔹 Overview

This project focuses on identifying high-potential locations for  store expansion using demographic data, spatial analysis, and data modeling techniques. The goal is to help  make data-driven decisions for opening new stores.

🔹 Objectives
Analyze population, income, and demographic trends
Identify areas with high demand and low competition
Perform spatial and drive-time analysis
Build a scoring model for location selection
Provide actionable recommendations

🔹 Data Sources
U.S. Census demographic data store locations
Competitor locations
Geographic boundary data (ZIP codes / shapefiles)
Additional datasets (universities, shopping centers, etc.)

🔹 Tools & Technologies
Python (Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn)
GIS tools (QGIS / ArcGIS)
SQL 
Jupyter Notebook

🔹 Methodology
Data cleaning and preprocessing
Feature engineering
Spatial analysis (mapping, distance, catchment zones)
Scoring model based on multiple factors
Visualization and dashboard creation

🔹 Key Features
Heatmaps of high-demand regions
Drive-time analysis around stores
Competitor density mapping
Location scoring model
Interactive Power BI dashboard

🔹 Results & Insights
Identified high-potential ZIP codes for expansion
Found underserved regions with strong demand
Highlighted key factors influencing store success
